    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-04T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-04T23:00:00-05:00" n="596"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Woodford</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_imprecise-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-04T23:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>We have received to-day from the Spanish minister a copy of the manifesto of the
                    autonomy government. It is not armistice. It proves to be an appeal by the
                    autonomy government of Cuba urging the insurgents to lay down their arms and to
                    join with the autonomy party in building up the new scheme of home rule. It is
                    simply an invitation to the insurgents to submit, in which event the autonomy
                    government, likewise suspending hostilities, is prepared to consider what
                    expansion if any of the decreed home-rule scheme is needed or practicable. It
                    need scarcely be pointed out that this is a very different thing from an offered
                    armistice. The President’s message will go in Wednesday afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-04T23:00:00-05:00">Monday night, 11
                            o’clock</date>.</dateline>
                    <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
